1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:29,980
 I think we're in a new age where people are trying to form themselves and they're trying to say this is who I am and trying to create their identity by themselves and I think what the Jedi Order teaches us and the Master Padawan teaches as well as spiritual direction and religious life is that we really cannot form ourselves we need others to help us in the formation of course we have a major role in that but we do need the mentor we do need others to help us keep

2
00:00:29,980 --> 00:00:49,440
 us and I think even in religious life that was for example Dominic's greatest insight you know that in order to truly discover what it means to live the gospel it cannot just be you and the Bible it has to be the community also that is shaping you basically discerning the spirit with the Holy Spirit

3
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:59,660
 father Alejandro thank you for joining me thank you for inviting me Benjamin

4
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:29,940
 so it's a pleasure to be here yes so before we jump in I'd like to ask how did you first become interested in Star Wars where did this love start well it started when I was very young so I was in the third grade nine years old back in San Diego California and that's when Star Wars came out in 1977 so when it first came out it was something very different from any sci-fi we had at the time so at that time the most classical although it was older was Space Odyssey

5
00:01:29,940 --> 00:01:59,920
 2000 2000 and 2001 and that was the classic kind of philosophical kind of slow moving films but really deep but as a child that really didn't excite me but when Star Wars came out that was a complete revolution it was like something we have never seen before and I got to see it 30 times 30 times so we were just it was almost like a Disneyland ride we just got out and we went back in and saw the next one and out and in

6
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:29,900
 as much as much as much as we could our grades went down as much as much as we could our grades went down at school I remember even the bishop calling a meeting of the school and the parents and that because all the grades were going down at the time so all of us were just starstruck with Star Wars so really it made a great impact in my life and I think what really caught my attention he was a young kid was that I saw the mythical aspect of it it was just epic and so yes there were shootings and you know star

7
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:44,280
 starships here and there and there and the whole kind of cowboy and Indian kind of show but also I mean we already detected even back then as a little kid the epic of and the mythic aspect of it so and I think that's what's remained all the way to today.

8
00:02:44,280 --> 00:03:10,760
 And Father now I'd like you know for our conversation to focus in particular on the character of Anakin Skywalker and his kind of emotional and spiritual journey we're introduced to him on Tatooine he's a young boy Qui-Gon Jinn who's a Jedi master senses you know the forces is strong in him he's then trained by Obi-Wan Kenobi can you share with us a little bit what do you think of this concept of the force what do you make of it?

9
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:31,420
 Well first of all I think yes so the first the prequels that came much later and then the original trilogy basically is the life of Anakin Skywalker so basically it's his story and I think throughout at least those first movies what the forces is also developed throughout.

10
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:46,880
 So I think George Lucas has been very clear and as we see also in the film as Ben Kenobi explains to Luke Skywalker in New Hope what the force is for them is basically an energy field that sustains and unites all living creatures.

11
00:03:47,560 --> 00:04:01,920
 And also the force can be used as a force for good but also for bad and so I think that's the original concept of it and especially George Lucas concept but it's also an impersonal force.

12
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:15,060
 It's an energy field as he explains it and I think it's closer more to what Zen Buddhism or Taoism would understand kind of the energy of the world and so on.

13
00:04:15,060 --> 00:04:32,020
 So less Christian but as the stories progress and also as new writers have written about it especially my favorite Dave Filoni has gone deeper and I think that for him especially the force has changed more to something that knows something that guides.

14
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:50,400
 So it's more of a personal spiritual so coming from coming from a domestic perspective I will not say is God or it tries to represent God and also many people that write on homiletics and theology and Star Wars will compare it to the Holy Spirit sometimes.

15
00:04:51,080 --> 00:05:09,300
 But I think it's more what Aquinas would call the order of creation so according to Thomas of course God creates with order so with intelligibility so it's not chaos that we have in that creation in the world everything is ordered everything's placed in the moral order created by himself.

16
00:05:09,660 --> 00:05:24,080
 And so I think that's what is being reflected in the force and especially when you consider that even for Thomas the way we behave towards God towards each other towards ourselves has an impact.

17
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:33,340
 And so if we behave in a virtuous way we have a positive, a balanced way in our relationships with ourselves, with others, and with creation.

18
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:39,600
 And when we behave in a vicious way, in a negative way, then we have a negative impact.

19
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:46,900
 So that kind of connects to what George Lucas and the whole Star Wars series talks about the balance and the imbalance of the force.

20
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:53,800
 That the actions, how we use the force, how we act within the force has an impact.

21
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,040
 So either for positive or for negative.

22
00:05:56,040 --> 00:06:00,400
 And so I think it's closer to what Thomas would call this order of creation.

23
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:12,540
 So this set of relationships between ourselves, God and creation and that how we act morally has an impact in that creation, in that order that God says that for better, for worse.

24
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:23,000
 So, and that where the whole story of original sin comes in and personal sin, where basically we distort the order of God because it becomes a selfish thing.

25
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:32,280
 The way of the way of the Sith, as opposed to one that is for the other, constructive of relationships, constructive and supportive of that moral order created by God.

26
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:39,620
 So that would be my view, kind of from a domestic perspective of what the force would be similar to in a mythical way.

27
00:06:39,620 --> 00:06:49,120
 So I wouldn't say it's a Christian perspective that is presented in Star Wars, but definitely from a mythic perspective is presented as this order that exists in creation.

28
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:54,680
 And then somehow it becomes imbalanced by our actions and balanced by our virtuous actions.

29
00:06:54,680 --> 00:07:00,140
 And Father, we are also introduced in the first film to the Jedi Order.

30
00:07:00,140 --> 00:07:02,920
 What are your thoughts on this knightly order?

31
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:07,580
 Are there any spiritual parallels to entering a religious order like the Dominicans?

32
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:13,260
 There's many, many things that are very common in religious life and to the order.

33
00:07:13,260 --> 00:07:18,940
 There's even one Dominican in Anchorage, Alaska that somehow can turn the Dominican habit into a Jedi habit.

34
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:21,040
 So you have to see the videos on YouTube.

35
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:23,700
 So, yeah, so there's a lot of commonalities.

36
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:26,920
 I think the main thing would be the importance of community.

37
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:34,220
 So the Jedi live in communities and then also the Dominicans, like ourselves, we live in community.

38
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:39,880
 The question of formation also is very important in the Star Wars and in the Jedi Order.

39
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:44,880
 So it is the masters and the Padawans that are formed into the force.

40
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:51,320
 And so also we ourselves are formed into becoming more Christ-like and coming to know Christ even more.

41
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:53,420
 So it doesn't come from nowhere.

42
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:56,760
 It's a personal and directed formation.

43
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,300
 And also the role of meditation.

44
00:07:59,300 --> 00:08:11,880
 So one of the main highlights of the more spiritual aspects of the Jedi Order is their contemplation and meditation and the role that plays in their lives, which tends to be more Zen Buddhist than Christian.

45
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:21,320
 But meditation is part of our life as we contemplate the scriptures, as we contemplate the liturgy, theology, philosophy.

46
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:30,200
 It's also part of that contemplation of basically, as St. Thomas Aquinas said, to contemplate the truth in order then to give those fruits unto others.

47
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:47,720
 So what is not like the order, and I think this is very important because it's a very interesting distinction, is that in Zen Buddhism, but also in especially in the Jedi Order, one, and I think this is what gets Anakin into trouble later on, and that's why I want to mention it, is that they definitely emphasize detachment.

48
00:08:48,580 --> 00:09:00,720
 So the Jedi is not supposed to have any kind of attachments, any kind of emotional attachments, because that therefore creates fear, that creates distraction from the way of the force.

49
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:10,940
 And so, as we'll see later on, Anakin Skywalker struggles with this, you know, this detachment regarding his mother, the detachment then regarding Padme.

50
00:09:10,940 --> 00:09:15,240
 And so that's something that we don't see in religious life.

51
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:21,680
 So our Christian perspective is like, we don't preach that kind of detachment, because what we really value is love.

52
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:31,500
 And so the real question for us as religious is not the detachment thing, but more, what do we love and how we should love it?

53
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:35,260
 So that depends on the circumstances, the people, the community, and so on.

54
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:41,600
 But we emphasize love, so they're reaching out towards the other, not separating ourselves from the other.

55
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:51,620
 But the question is what we should love and what we shouldn't love and how we should love it, according to the different characteristics and closeness to us.

56
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:57,420
 And that's the Order of Amoris that Thomas Aquinas speaks of and also St. Augustine.

57
00:09:57,420 --> 00:10:05,420
 So it's that Order of Love that he talks about, which I think in one sense, that is not part of the Jedi way.

58
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:23,020
 And that comes up in the sequels also, where Luke Skywalker, in thinking of rebuilding the Order after the collapse of the Order, that's one of the issues he really struggles with, whether to maintain that kind of detachment within the Order.

59
00:10:23,020 --> 00:10:26,940
 And I think he tends to change, no, we need to start reaching out to other people.

60
00:10:26,940 --> 00:10:28,680
 So that will be a major difference.

61
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:40,180
 And then, Father, with regards to detachment, one of the big themes within that formation is the emotional relationship that's developed between a Padawan and a Jedi Master.

62
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:42,980
 And we see this with Qui-Gon and Obi-Wan.

63
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:49,340
 We see that with Obi-Wan and then Anakin and then Obi-Wan as well in his development and formation of Luke.

64
00:10:49,340 --> 00:10:54,220
 Can you speak a little bit on this dynamic that has a lot of emotional valence within the series?

65
00:10:54,220 --> 00:11:04,680
 Yeah, I mean, I think like any kind of mentorship, there's a relationship that is very, very intimate.

66
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:12,720
 And it's a relationship that's not created by blood bond or by kind of emotional bond, but it's really a mentorship.

67
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:15,940
 And so in those mentorships, we are vulnerable.

68
00:11:15,940 --> 00:11:24,500
 We are, in one sense, kind of revealing the dark side as well as the light side and looking for guidance.

69
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:30,100
 And then the Master is there to basically guide us to bring out the best of us.

70
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:37,060
 And also in the mentorship, hopefully the mentor, the Master, knows what is the best of us.

71
00:11:37,060 --> 00:11:39,020
 And that's what he's trying to bring out.

72
00:11:39,020 --> 00:11:41,360
 So it's a very, very close relationship.

73
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:44,840
 And it's very similar in our Christian tradition where we have spiritual direction.

74
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:54,820
 And so in spiritual direction also is this relationship that is established between the spiritual master and the one being guided that is intimate, close.

75
00:11:54,820 --> 00:12:02,660
 Sometimes it's even closer that you would have with your own family because you talk about issues that you wouldn't necessarily talk with the family.

76
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:11,340
 But here you talk because you're trying to discern what is God's call or voice within this life circumstances.

77
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:16,200
 So I think that is reflected in the Jedi Order and but also in the Sith.

78
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,340
 So we see this mentorship.

79
00:12:17,340 --> 00:12:21,060
 So you can be mentored towards good or you can be mentored towards evil.

80
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:23,580
 And we see that also in real life.

81
00:12:23,580 --> 00:12:26,620
 You know, some people, yeah, learn evil from other people.

82
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:29,380
 They see other people doing what they're not supposed to do.

83
00:12:29,460 --> 00:12:31,720
 And that's what they do because they see this.

84
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:36,460
 So it's a very important aspect of daily life, I think.

85
00:12:36,460 --> 00:12:46,360
 And also, I think, especially in today's society where a lot of people feel, I think we're in a new age where people are trying to form themselves.

86
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:54,000
 And they're trying to say, this is who I am and trying to create their identity by themselves.

87
00:12:54,520 --> 00:13:03,100
 And I think what the Jedi Order teaches us and the Master Padawan teaches us, as well as spiritual direction and religious life, is that we really cannot form ourselves.

88
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:06,580
 We need others to help us in the formation.

89
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:08,340
 Of course, we have a major role in that.

90
00:13:08,340 --> 00:13:10,240
 But we do need the mentor.

91
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:12,480
 We do need others to help us, keep us.

92
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:17,880
 And I think even in religious life, that was, for example, Dominic's greatest insight.

93
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:24,400
 You know, that in order to truly discover what it means to live the gospel, it cannot just be you and the Bible.

94
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:31,660
 It has to be the community also that is shaping you, basically discerning the spirit with the Holy Spirit.

95
00:13:31,660 --> 00:13:34,940
 And I think that's what we see in the Jedi Order.

96
00:13:34,940 --> 00:13:36,900
 We see that in religious life.

97
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:39,080
 And I think that's something that is lacking today.

98
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:47,100
 So I think a lot of people are trying to search for mentors, but they tend to kind of look to themselves and try to form themselves.

99
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:53,980
 And so that has some good aspects, but also a lot of negative aspects, because very easy, we can delude ourselves.

100
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:58,800
 And Father, I'd like now to turn our attention to Emperor Palpatine.

101
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:08,220
 So if we zoom out, during this time, there's the Clone Wars, which is a galaxy-wide conflict between the Galactic Republic and the Separatist Movement.

102
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:19,160
 And during this period of major battles, there's a lot of political maneuvering by, at the time, Senator Palpatine, who secretly is orchestrating both sides of the war.

103
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:21,420
 What do you make of Palpatine?

104
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:24,660
 Well, I mean, Palpatine is a great villain.

105
00:14:24,660 --> 00:14:28,760
 And I think part of it is because, again, he's the mythical villain.

106
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:38,520
 And so, like everything, and especially in the original series, which is more mythical than the new ones, you know, evil is evil, good is good, you know.

107
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:42,560
 And so Palpatine is the incarnation of 100% evilness.

108
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:48,040
 And so I think he's very, very much close to the biblical Satan, almost.

109
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:51,380
 And so he incarnates evil incarnate.

110
00:14:51,380 --> 00:14:58,920
 And he, like the devil, doesn't use force to do any of those changes, even with Chancellor.

111
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:01,500
 But even as he becomes emperor, he never uses force.

112
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:05,360
 It's, I think, one of his greatest virtue is patience.

113
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:07,300
 There's a lot of patience.

114
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:17,900
 So he's been working on creating this empire for years and years, slowly manipulating, telling half-truths, basically saying what you want to hear.

115
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:24,580
 And basically that's what he's doing through the whole, his whole lifetime, to be able to reach ultimate power.

116
00:15:24,580 --> 00:15:30,280
 And he's been working that very slowly, very slowly throughout the ages, which is what we see in the movies.

117
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:33,940
 And so, yeah, he works basically like the biblical devil.

118
00:15:33,940 --> 00:15:41,720
 So he whispers to us half-truths and basically tells us what we want to hear to tempt us into the dark side.

119
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:48,140
 And so I think he, the way he's portrayed, that's what you're, that's what true evil is.

120
00:15:48,140 --> 00:15:54,080
 So it's not this force that just kind of by brute force, you know, forces you into the dark side.

121
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:58,220
 But it's more subtle, it's more of the sensation of temptation, I think.

122
00:15:58,220 --> 00:16:03,200
 And that's what he presents to both Anakin and then he presents also to Luke later on.

123
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:11,240
 And Father, if we can just sit on that relationship between Palpatine and Anakin in particular, how do you see him manipulating Anakin?

124
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:15,020
 I mean, Anakin is a character who is at the summit of his Jedi training.

125
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:17,580
 He's going to be an incredible, you know, Jedi master.

126
00:16:17,580 --> 00:16:22,780
 He has an incredible relationship with Obi-Wan who loves him, like almost like a father-son.

127
00:16:22,780 --> 00:16:29,460
 How does Palpatine wedge this divide in there slowly and then, you know, break it up?

128
00:16:29,460 --> 00:16:33,820
 Well, I mean, like Satan, Satan always knows our weaknesses.

129
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:38,920
 So he knows exactly where to hit us and where, how to tempt us.

130
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:43,780
 And so, I mean, Anakin is a very interesting character.

131
00:16:43,780 --> 00:16:50,060
 And so you have to see the prequels to really understand everything that's been there since the very beginning.

132
00:16:50,060 --> 00:16:57,900
 So in one sense that he turns to the dark side is not a big surprise because from very young age,

133
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:04,680
 one of the things that really motivates him for a lot of things that he does is, unfortunately, fear.

134
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:10,340
 And so fear, of course, as Thomas Aquinas would say, is not necessarily a negative thing.

135
00:17:10,340 --> 00:17:17,320
 So it's more whether when it gets detached from a reason and is used correctly.

136
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:23,360
 So, for example, we are supposed to be fearful of dangerous things, not to endanger our lives or that of others.

137
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:24,960
 So that's good fear.

138
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:32,360
 But also there's this fear where you just simply will do the wrong thing in order to avoid that fear.

139
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:36,640
 And so from a very young age, he was afraid of losing his mom.

140
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:38,380
 He was afraid of death.

141
00:17:38,740 --> 00:17:42,200
 He was afraid of losing Padawan later on and Parame.

142
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,540
 And then he was afraid of death itself.

143
00:17:44,540 --> 00:17:47,900
 And so this is what kind of begins to model.

144
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:56,740
 That's why he wanted to become the strongest, most powerful Jedi there was because he wanted to somehow get rid of this fear

145
00:17:56,740 --> 00:17:58,640
 or somehow at least control this fear.

146
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:04,920
 And I think that's where Palpatine and the Emperor see the weakness of Anakin.

147
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:08,400
 And so that's where he starts working on him.

148
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:12,320
 And so he says, oh, so, you know, have you ever heard the legend of Plagueis?

149
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:17,300
 You know, and so how he, you know, has the power to basically bring somebody back from the dead.

150
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:20,780
 And so he reaches exactly where his fears are.

151
00:18:20,780 --> 00:18:23,440
 And from that, he brings them to the dark side.

152
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:29,940
 But the conversion towards evil basically doesn't start at that point for Anakin.

153
00:18:29,940 --> 00:18:31,700
 It started when he was already a little boy.

154
00:18:31,700 --> 00:18:33,540
 All those traumas that he had.

155
00:18:33,540 --> 00:18:37,320
 And he was not able to let go of those fears.

156
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:45,740
 And instead of trying to control that, basically to, you know, kind of go with the force, you would say, in the Star Wars universe.

157
00:18:45,740 --> 00:18:52,680
 And I think that's how the Emperor gets because he knows exactly what are the weaknesses of Anakin.

158
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:54,800
 And that's how he brings them to his side.

159
00:18:54,800 --> 00:19:00,260
 And so, Father, when do you think it truly goes wrong for Anakin?

160
00:19:00,260 --> 00:19:06,460
 Is there an exact moment that we could point to in the films where the audience can be like, there it is.

161
00:19:06,460 --> 00:19:07,780
 That's the moment where he's turning?

162
00:19:07,780 --> 00:19:09,920
 Well, I think it is.

163
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:10,300
 Yeah.

164
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:13,420
 So, like I said, it's all been his whole life.

165
00:19:13,620 --> 00:19:23,960
 And so, as we see throughout the whole series, the Clone Wars, et cetera, he's beginning to make those choices where he's reacting a lot of times out of fear and out of pride.

166
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:28,900
 Those are the two basically vices of Anakin and very strong ones.

167
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:31,680
 And so, we see that from the very beginning.

168
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:39,340
 Father, could we say that it could perhaps be starting with his love for Padme because that forces a relationship that's based on lying and deception?

169
00:19:39,340 --> 00:19:45,760
 Because that relationship as a Jedi Knight, he's not permitted to be in this type of relationship with a woman.

170
00:19:46,020 --> 00:19:49,500
 And then she's pregnant and there's that, you know, there's that fear.

171
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:51,080
 Well, definitely that place I made you.

172
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,860
 I think it goes even further back, though.

173
00:19:52,860 --> 00:19:54,220
 I think it goes with his mom.

174
00:19:54,220 --> 00:20:13,560
 So, I think when Queen Yong picks him up at the planet to take him for training, and basically he was a slave like his mom, and for some reason he gets freed, and of course there has to be a way the Emperor intervenes to free also his mom, but his mom doesn't get freed.

175
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:18,480
 And so, then he has to separate from his mom, who is the only one he has in life.

176
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:20,540
 There's no brothers, there's no sisters, there's no father.

177
00:20:20,540 --> 00:20:24,360
 So, this is the only emotional connection that he has.

178
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:26,380
 So, I think it begins there.

179
00:20:26,380 --> 00:20:33,740
 And so, then that gets reflected in his relationship with Padme, because then with Padme, he's afraid of being alone.

180
00:20:33,740 --> 00:20:39,400
 That's one of his biggest fears, of losing those he loves and being alone.

181
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:46,860
 And so, Padme becomes for him also that kind of, this is what I'm going to hold on to, to support my emotional.

182
00:20:46,860 --> 00:20:56,300
 So, I would say it's not really love, that he really loves Padme, it's more that he finds in her, okay, this is something I can use for my emotional support.

183
00:20:56,300 --> 00:21:05,600
 And that's how, so he doesn't have what we would call Christian love, which is sacrificial love, that he would be loved for her and do whatever he needs to do for her.

184
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:08,020
 But it's not what, you have to suffer for me.

185
00:21:08,340 --> 00:21:10,140
 So, you have to be there for me.

186
00:21:10,140 --> 00:21:15,720
 And I think that's, that's also a reflection from what already was happening with his relation with his mom.

187
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:23,020
 And, and I think that's why the prequels are very important about that relationship with his mom, because that trauma you begin to see there.

188
00:21:23,020 --> 00:21:28,660
 Of separation, of his fear of separation, the fear of the one he loved, and then she gets killed.

189
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:32,360
 So, he also loses her, and he has the dreams about losing her.

190
00:21:32,360 --> 00:21:38,720
 Then those dreams repeat again with Padme, that he dreams that she's going to die when she gives birth.

191
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:40,900
 So, basically, it's the same story.

192
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:46,160
 It gets repeated again, because it's the same fear that's been driving him through this whole period.

193
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:52,400
 And so, Father, you would, you would say that Anakin does not actually love Padme in, in the Christian sense.

194
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:53,200
 Yeah, I agree.

195
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:59,420
 So, I think he's basically using her to, this is my, my emotional support.

196
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:09,680
 And so, so then he becomes controlling, he becomes jealous, he becomes manipulative, even a Padme, because it's not true love in that sense.

197
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:15,640
 Why do you think, Father, that Anakin bows the knee to Palpatine in that moment where Palpatine kills Mace Windu?

198
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:22,520
 Well, I mean, and you had already asked originally, you know, when was the moment that he kind of, okay, now he's evil.

199
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:25,700
 Well, now he's, so then, like I said, it was, it was a long process.

200
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:31,920
 So, you know, it's not a, it's not a, a cliff fall.

201
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:34,360
 It's a slippery slope.

202
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:38,140
 And that's how we fall into sin and even worse things.

203
00:22:38,140 --> 00:22:40,060
 It's not an overnight thing.

204
00:22:40,060 --> 00:22:45,920
 Some spiritual directors will say, really, we do not commit mortal sins.

205
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:46,780
 It's very rare.

206
00:22:46,780 --> 00:22:49,400
 It's really more venial sins that keep accumulating.

207
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:51,220
 It's the same thing we keep repeating.

208
00:22:51,220 --> 00:22:53,880
 And we just keep justifying and falling into it.

209
00:22:53,880 --> 00:23:04,020
 So, I think by that time, when he falls to his knees before Palpatine, basically, he's just confirming what the path he has already been into.

210
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:16,140
 And because he had already been on that path for quite some time, he doesn't go back to the Jedi because the Jedi basically remind him of what he was supposed to be.

211
00:23:16,140 --> 00:23:20,760
 But now he, he cannot be, or he won't be, or he doesn't want to be.

212
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:33,340
 And I think that's the main reason because he sees, and St. Thomas Aquinas will say passions, evil passions, the vice will cloud our mind.

213
00:23:33,340 --> 00:23:37,240
 And so, in one sense, we can no longer see the truth.

214
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:40,300
 And so, we're, we're so caught up already on this path.

215
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:42,280
 And I think that's what happens to Anakin.

216
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:44,820
 So, Anakin has closed himself up.

217
00:23:44,820 --> 00:23:49,140
 So, this is the only way I can kind of face my fears and so on.

218
00:23:49,140 --> 00:23:50,900
 And so, this is the only way.

219
00:23:50,900 --> 00:23:52,100
 And there's no turning back.

220
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:57,380
 And I think that just simply confirms when he promises allegiance to the Emperor.

221
00:23:57,380 --> 00:23:59,060
 But that's been going on for a while.

222
00:23:59,060 --> 00:24:00,800
 And he's already been separating from the Jedi.

223
00:24:01,060 --> 00:24:07,160
 So, he's already, he's been kind of fighting with the consul that they don't make him a master.

224
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:09,180
 He's also fighting with Obi-Wan.

225
00:24:09,180 --> 00:24:12,600
 He'll, you know, this is his best friend, but now he doesn't really trust him.

226
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:15,540
 And he's holding him back from being all he can be.

227
00:24:15,540 --> 00:24:18,480
 So, that's been also growing for a while.

228
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:21,720
 And so, yeah, he's beginning to lose his connection to the Jedi.

229
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:25,320
 And so, yeah, this is just the final culmination.

230
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:28,520
 And how should we understand concupiscence in light of this example?

231
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:35,600
 Well, I mean, again, it's more the question of fear and pride.

232
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:42,040
 And so, like you said, and so I think that's, it's this desire for security.

233
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:47,820
 And, but that at one point, we don't find security in controlling things.

234
00:24:47,820 --> 00:24:50,260
 And I think that's what he does, you know.

235
00:24:50,260 --> 00:24:57,160
 So, for him is through control, then I can get rid of the fear or somehow control the fear.

236
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:59,660
 But that's not the way we get rid of it.

237
00:24:59,740 --> 00:25:02,280
 It's again, as St. Thomas Aquinas talks about the virtue.

238
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:07,120
 So, we need to catalyze that fear, that energy, that emotion towards the good.

239
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:08,800
 So, it's not to suppress it.

240
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:12,860
 So, again, as I said originally, one of the big differences between our Christian perspective

241
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:20,520
 and that of the Jedi or Buddhism and that of the Jedi or Buddhism is precisely the question of this attachment, you know.

242
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:21,580
 So, for us, no.

243
00:25:21,580 --> 00:25:23,020
 The emotions are good.

244
00:25:23,020 --> 00:25:24,000
 The passions are good.

245
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:26,980
 But the question is, how do we guide them?

246
00:25:26,980 --> 00:25:29,200
 Do we use them for the good or for the bad?

247
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:30,580
 So, it's not a question of suppression.

248
00:25:30,580 --> 00:25:34,260
 It's a question of channeling to the right way.

249
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:36,520
 And so, that was the answer for him, too.

250
00:25:36,520 --> 00:25:38,320
 To use all this passion for the good.

251
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:42,820
 But instead, it was just to control so he wouldn't have that fear.

252
00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:48,160
 And, Father, in that moment, so he bows the knee to Palpatine.

253
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:51,400
 And within, let's say, a matter of hours, he's killing younglings.

254
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:54,100
 I mean, that's an extraordinary change.

255
00:25:54,100 --> 00:26:02,520
 And it's a fall that the only parallel I can really think of is Lucifer's fall, where you're the highest angel to Satan.

256
00:26:03,340 --> 00:26:07,300
 What do you make of that immediate and radical transformation?

257
00:26:07,300 --> 00:26:12,280
 Well, I mean, I think we said, St. Thomas Aquinas will talk about despair.

258
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:15,000
 And I think that's what he reached at that point.

259
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:21,960
 So, once we have despair, basically, yeah, we would do things that we would never imagine we could actually do.

260
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:24,640
 Because at that time, we were in desperation.

261
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:28,220
 So, we lose the sense of value, the sense of balance.

262
00:26:28,220 --> 00:26:31,600
 And so, we're just reacting.

263
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:33,240
 We're just kind of falling.

264
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:35,300
 And in this case, he's falling into the anger.

265
00:26:35,300 --> 00:26:38,420
 He is basically, the Jedi have betrayed us.

266
00:26:38,420 --> 00:26:41,160
 The whole republic has betrayed us, et cetera.

267
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:44,760
 And so, it's just this anger that he has inside.

268
00:26:44,760 --> 00:26:46,860
 And it's basically just manifesting itself.

269
00:26:46,860 --> 00:26:53,020
 So, again, once we start on that life of vice, yeah, we get blinded.

270
00:26:53,020 --> 00:26:54,860
 And it's a slippery slope.

271
00:26:54,860 --> 00:27:00,540
 And, yeah, we end up doing things we wouldn't even dream we could do.

272
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:04,120
 You know, because we were so blinded by it or by the passion.

273
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:06,120
 In this case, it would be anger.

274
00:27:06,120 --> 00:27:11,400
 And, Father, could we also make a parallel with the despair and hopelessness that Judas felt in his betrayal?

275
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:29,080
 So, I mean, I think that Anakin Skywalker is basically the love, beloved disciple that basically betrays the Jedi and the light side of the force because of fear and because of pride.

276
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:32,160
 And so, definitely, that's what he does.

277
00:27:32,160 --> 00:27:47,320
 The difference, of course, between Judas and Anakin is that at the end, Anakin is able to, and we see this on the first trilogy, opens himself again to mercy with his son, Luke.

278
00:27:47,660 --> 00:27:51,020
 And so, when he's, you know, here and here, he says, yes, you have saved me already.

279
00:27:51,020 --> 00:27:52,640
 So, that was the difference.

280
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:56,980
 Judas falls into despair and then he kills himself.

281
00:27:56,980 --> 00:28:04,380
 So, the logical consequence, well, logical in the sense that it's just the slippery slope to despair and more despair to the end of life.

282
00:28:04,380 --> 00:28:10,460
 And, but Leia, Luke have always seen, no, they're still good in him.

283
00:28:10,580 --> 00:28:14,340
 So, there was still a little spark there that could have been turned.

284
00:28:14,340 --> 00:28:22,380
 And I think that's why we see in Return of the Jedi, Luke really working on that little flame that was there because I know there's something there.

285
00:28:22,380 --> 00:28:26,440
 And so, and that's what saves him at the end, which I think for Judas Iscariot, that was gone.

286
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:29,400
 So, he just, at the despair, I cannot be saved.

287
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:40,160
 I will never be forgiven, which I think you see Anakin also when Luke, when first sees Vader in Endor and they have that conversation.

288
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:43,520
 Judas over here, you know, I, I know there's still good in you.

289
00:28:43,520 --> 00:28:47,460
 I think Anakin's still there, but like he says, that name has no meaning for me.

290
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:50,400
 I said, so I think it's just like Judas, there's no forgiveness for me.

291
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:51,740
 This is the path I have chosen.

292
00:28:51,740 --> 00:28:58,160
 There's no out, you know, but then he himself recognizes towards the end and that makes the whole difference.

293
00:28:58,160 --> 00:29:06,580
 So, that brings the redemption of Anakin Skywalker that, thank goodness, Luke had seen constantly there and, and worked on that.

294
00:29:07,860 --> 00:29:23,980
 And Father, before, before I turn to Order 66, which I want to touch on, you mentioned Luke working on, on his father, Anakin, and that finding the redemptive quality and that being kind of the center part of his kind of journey as a Jedi or in his formation.

295
00:29:25,020 --> 00:29:36,020
 Is there something different in Anakin's attempt for Jedi glory, if you will, in the sense of wanting to save Padme, that those two loves, those two guiding lights are different in nature?

296
00:29:36,020 --> 00:29:45,460
 Oh yeah, I mean, I think, well, I mean, Anakin and Luke are very similar and I think it could, it could have gone the same for Luke.

297
00:29:45,460 --> 00:29:52,120
 And we see that when he is with training with Yoda and Dagobah and he goes into the cave.

298
00:29:52,680 --> 00:30:01,460
 And so, basically, he confronts himself and what he sees is Vader and when he defeats Vader and the mask falls off, it's his own face.

299
00:30:01,460 --> 00:30:06,240
 So, basically, he was saying, yes, this is part of your heritage.

300
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:12,200
 You could end up here, you know, in this whole thing, becoming evil to a Sith Lord.

301
00:30:12,460 --> 00:30:18,680
 So, but I think that's also where we see, because it's both the story of Anakin Skywalker and the story of Luke Skywalker.

302
00:30:18,680 --> 00:30:24,060
 And in the story of Luke Skywalker and Anakin, what we see is their choices.

303
00:30:24,060 --> 00:30:28,060
 And that's what makes, because I think also Luke is fearful also.

304
00:30:28,060 --> 00:30:33,120
 And I think he's also looking for companionship, a place of belonging.

305
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:37,620
 He didn't belong in Tatooine, he was looking for something else.

306
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:42,640
 And so, he has the same fears in one sense as Anakin.

307
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:45,640
 I think Luke doesn't have the pride of Anakin.

308
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:48,040
 And I think that already makes him kind of different.

309
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:50,060
 But ultimately, it's the choices.

310
00:30:50,060 --> 00:30:59,380
 So, whereas Anakin, to confront his fear and support his pride, chooses basically control.

311
00:30:59,380 --> 00:31:00,880
 And that's this whole thing.

312
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:06,020
 He chooses to control and to become the most powerful Jedi to control all this.

313
00:31:06,020 --> 00:31:09,060
 And that's how it's going to, death is going to be kept away in fear.

314
00:31:09,060 --> 00:31:14,100
 Whereas Luke, I think, is more open to redemption.

315
00:31:14,100 --> 00:31:16,880
 It's more open to see, okay, where can this lead?

316
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:23,880
 How can we move forward from this and basically reach, become a real master Jedi?

317
00:31:24,140 --> 00:31:32,980
 And I think that's where Yoda plays a major role in basically helping him understand, yeah, wars don't make a warrior great, he tells him.

318
00:31:32,980 --> 00:31:35,480
 Because he's expecting also Yoda to be this great warrior.

319
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:37,300
 And then he sees this little green guy.

320
00:31:37,300 --> 00:31:43,000
 So, but that's because he's trying to, this is not what the Jedi life is all about, you know.

321
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:47,960
 It's precisely this whole question of choosing the good, choosing the light.

322
00:31:49,100 --> 00:31:51,400
 It's not about moving rocks and all that.

323
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:53,500
 It is really a path, you know.

324
00:31:53,500 --> 00:31:55,380
 And so, I think Luke learns that quickly.

325
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:57,740
 And of course, you see also him rebelling against that.

326
00:31:57,740 --> 00:32:00,300
 He leaves Yoda and goes to save his friends.

327
00:32:00,300 --> 00:32:02,480
 Although Yoda says he won't be able to help them.

328
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:04,480
 And actually, yeah, he's not able to help them.

329
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:07,760
 So, we see also him struggling with that.

330
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:10,280
 But ultimately, he is making the right choice.

331
00:32:10,280 --> 00:32:22,040
 And I think also when he is his father and in front of the emperor and so on, where he says, you know, here I am defenseless, strike me down.

332
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:25,160
 So, it's kind of like the, would I kill baby Hitler?

333
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:27,600
 Had I known that he's going to be Hitler?

334
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:30,500
 Should I, you know, I have the chance here, baby Hitler, should I kill him or not?

335
00:32:30,500 --> 00:32:32,720
 And that's what he's confronted with, you know.

336
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:36,260
 But he has already learned the way of the force by that time.

337
00:32:36,260 --> 00:32:38,040
 And says, no, I will not do it.

338
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:39,100
 And he won't fight his father.

339
00:32:39,100 --> 00:32:41,480
 He will not fight him because that's not the way of the judge.

340
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:43,020
 Because that leads to anger.

341
00:32:43,020 --> 00:32:47,740
 And then anger leads to everything else that Anakin Skywalker did choose.

342
00:32:47,740 --> 00:32:50,280
 And that made the whole difference for the two of them.

343
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:55,920
 And Father, can I posit a theory also on the differences and choices that Anakin and Luke make?

344
00:32:55,920 --> 00:33:06,120
 And with regards to Luke not having the pride of Anakin, I wonder if Anakin did not have the benefit of those 30 years of the silent, hidden life that, you know, our Lord had as well.

345
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:09,960
 Growing up 30 years where he was just quietly living his life.

346
00:33:09,960 --> 00:33:19,500
 And Anakin, from the get-go, when he has a public life, when he's discovered by Qui-Gon and the Jedi, is told again and again and again, you are the chosen one.

347
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:25,880
 And he makes extraordinary progress and has an extraordinary training and youth and development in that sense.

348
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:31,040
 Luke, from the very beginning, has no, is humble existence.

349
00:33:31,040 --> 00:33:34,320
 Has no recognition on any level until he meets Obi-Wan.

350
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:39,300
 And I wonder if that, those years of silence were the difference.

351
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:44,040
 Yeah, I think you put on something very interesting that I didn't even think about.

352
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,660
 But yeah, very true.

353
00:33:45,660 --> 00:33:53,240
 So, I mean, I think, first of all, like you said, Anakin is already being groomed to be the chosen one.

354
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:57,360
 So, I mean, you almost kind of groom him for pride because you are the chosen one.

355
00:33:58,400 --> 00:34:05,080
 Ko-Yong tells him, I've never seen someone with such a strength in the force as a little kid that doesn't know anything about it.

356
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:09,420
 So, he's kind of already set up to be a champion, basically.

357
00:34:09,420 --> 00:34:11,920
 And so, he's trained for that.

358
00:34:13,680 --> 00:34:29,780
 So, I think also what he lacked was mentorship because I think Ben Kenobi, Obi-Wan, I think, first of all, I think Ben Kenobi is the incarnation of what the Jedis are really supposed to be.

359
00:34:29,780 --> 00:34:31,200
 Because Ko-Yong is a rebel.

360
00:34:31,200 --> 00:34:34,380
 He's always fighting the system and that's why he's not in the council.

361
00:34:34,380 --> 00:34:38,420
 Even Ben Kenobi says, you would be in the council if you wouldn't be fighting them all the time.

362
00:34:38,420 --> 00:34:43,120
 And even when he says, you will not fight them anymore, right, regarding the training of Anakin.

363
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:44,920
 He says, I have to do what I have to do.

364
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:46,460
 So, he's always been the rebel.

365
00:34:46,460 --> 00:34:48,460
 And he's also teaching that to Anakin.

366
00:34:48,460 --> 00:34:56,380
 But before, when he dies or he's dying, he makes Ben Kenobi, Obi-Wan, promise that he will train the child.

367
00:34:56,380 --> 00:34:59,440
 So, that's what he takes him on, although he hasn't finished his own training.

368
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:02,220
 And so, he's also kind of doubtful.

369
00:35:02,220 --> 00:35:08,960
 And so, I think I've read somewhere that basically Anakin really needed a father figure.

370
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:10,720
 He needed a Yoda, really.

371
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:13,180
 And Ben is more of a brother.

372
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:16,920
 He's your older brother, but more of a brother relationship.

373
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:28,520
 So, in one sense, it's not that Obi-Wan failed in the formation of Anakin, but that Anakin really needed more of a father figure than a brother figure.

374
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:31,000
 And I think so, that was also a lack.

375
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:36,120
 Whereas Luke, as you said already from the reveal, first of all, he never had these expectations.

376
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:39,420
 He was just looking more for adventure and so on.

377
00:35:39,420 --> 00:35:42,780
 He was kind of the kid brother, you know, your younger brother in the family.

378
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:47,360
 And then, of course, Obi-Wan knows he's the family.

379
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:52,080
 So, it's more because he's part of the Skywalker family that he says he probably does have the force.

380
00:35:52,080 --> 00:35:53,260
 We need to train him.

381
00:35:53,260 --> 00:35:56,700
 But, and Ben is older by that time also.

382
00:35:56,700 --> 00:35:58,220
 So, he has had a lot of experience.

383
00:35:58,220 --> 00:35:59,560
 He's seen what happened before.

384
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:05,660
 So, even the mentorship of Obi-Wan is a more mature one.

385
00:36:05,660 --> 00:36:09,740
 But then, he has the years with Yoda.

386
00:36:09,740 --> 00:36:11,960
 And I think also that here's the father figure.

387
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:16,440
 And so, he really guides him like also Jesus going into the desert.

388
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:22,820
 So, he has that more direct confrontation as opposed to kind of more discernment, I think.

389
00:36:22,900 --> 00:36:25,760
 And I think Anakin really didn't get that discernment time.

390
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:27,980
 It was more, yeah, you're the chosen one.

391
00:36:27,980 --> 00:36:29,620
 So, you better prepare for this and da-da-da.

392
00:36:29,620 --> 00:36:32,480
 And I think Luke is more, okay.

393
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:35,420
 So, because they're also fearful that he will turn into the dark side.

394
00:36:35,420 --> 00:36:40,500
 So, both Yoda and ghost Obi-Wan are cautious, you know.

395
00:36:40,500 --> 00:36:42,680
 It's like, okay, but okay, we're seeing this.

396
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:45,980
 So, they are also training him in a way so that he won't fall.

397
00:36:45,980 --> 00:36:47,500
 So, I think, yeah.

398
00:36:47,500 --> 00:36:48,940
 So, that makes a big difference.

399
00:36:48,940 --> 00:36:52,720
 And then, Father, now I'd like to turn our attention to that fall.

400
00:36:52,720 --> 00:37:00,140
 And to go back to Palpatine executing Order 66, this is a unique moment in the prequel trilogy

401
00:37:00,140 --> 00:37:03,580
 where clone troopers now turn on their Jedi generals.

402
00:37:03,580 --> 00:37:08,560
 Anakin, who is now Darth Vader, is hunting down the last remaining Jedi.

403
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:10,240
 This is an extraordinary moment.

404
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:12,420
 What are your thoughts on Order 66?

405
00:37:12,420 --> 00:37:18,280
 Well, I mean, again, it was something that the Emperor had planned a long time ago.

406
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:22,540
 So, I mean, for him, from the very beginning, he knew that the biggest obstacle to

407
00:37:22,540 --> 00:37:24,460
 assuming full power were the Jedi.

408
00:37:24,460 --> 00:37:26,780
 So, that was the biggest obstacle.

409
00:37:26,780 --> 00:37:32,000
 And so, he'd been planning for this at one point where he had the chance to get rid of the Jedi.

410
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:34,300
 And so, that's what he does with Order 66.

411
00:37:34,300 --> 00:37:35,780
 So, that was no surprise.

412
00:37:35,780 --> 00:37:40,840
 And so, it's already, because we already know it was not an Order he just gave right there and then.

413
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:50,080
 But even in the building of the clones, it was already implanted in their brains that they, when he said that, they would react this way and turn on the Jedi.

414
00:37:50,420 --> 00:37:52,500
 So, it was planned way before.

415
00:37:52,500 --> 00:38:05,760
 So, but I think, basically, we just see the culmination that once we kind of go on the dark side, it just keeps growing and growing and growing.

416
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,740
 And so, it's like virtue.

417
00:38:07,860 --> 00:38:08,980
 So, we have vice and virtue.

418
00:38:08,980 --> 00:38:12,840
 And so, if we practice virtue, we live the good life, that goodness keeps growing.

419
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:15,040
 We become better people, you know.

420
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:16,860
 And the same thing with sin.

421
00:38:16,860 --> 00:38:23,300
 If we fall into vice and so on, we become worse people to the point that it becomes a world thing.

422
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:32,020
 Order 66, you know, that even gets rid of people that were our friends, who were our allies, who were the ones defending us.

423
00:38:32,020 --> 00:38:42,320
 And so, we now can see them enemies because they're no longer, we're blinded, basically, by that fear and by that pride and by that search for power as it was that of the Emperor.

424
00:38:42,860 --> 00:38:57,260
 And Father, in that moment, we have one Jedi who turns and becomes Darth Vader and wreaks, you know, emotional, spiritual havoc in his own personal life that then manifests itself in the actions he's taking against his brother Jedi.

425
00:38:57,260 --> 00:39:04,640
 But in that same time, in that one man's fall, we have what seems to be the fall of the galaxy, chaos in the galaxy now with this order.

426
00:39:04,640 --> 00:39:05,900
 Are there any parallels?

427
00:39:05,900 --> 00:39:12,900
 Can you speak to how one person's action can actually be reflected and magnified throughout the cosmos in that sense?

428
00:39:12,900 --> 00:39:21,400
 Well, I mean, also, we are talking with very unique people here because both Anakin, I mean, was considered a great warrior.

429
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:28,040
 And so, he was a great master already by that point, as we see in the Clone Wars, very close to the troopers.

430
00:39:28,860 --> 00:39:38,820
 And so, when a high spiritual figure falls, yeah, it has a major consequence throughout, you know.

431
00:39:38,820 --> 00:39:46,660
 So, even today when we hear of, you know, scandals in the church and, you know, preachers that fall from grace and so on.

432
00:39:46,660 --> 00:39:48,580
 I mean, it really has a consequence.

433
00:39:48,580 --> 00:39:50,640
 It's not just a personal fall.

434
00:39:50,640 --> 00:39:54,520
 It really makes a lot of people a scandal.

435
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:56,680
 So, basically, a lot of people lose faith.

436
00:39:56,680 --> 00:39:59,500
 A lot of people start doubting things.

437
00:39:59,500 --> 00:40:08,120
 So, it really has a ripple effect in a greater way than if it's just some kind of, you know, somebody who is more obscure and so on that falls into this.

438
00:40:08,120 --> 00:40:10,080
 So, I think that's what we're seeing there.

439
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:12,780
 And so, we see Anakin.

440
00:40:12,780 --> 00:40:20,500
 We see supposedly the Chancellor who is looking out for the galaxy and so on, who turn, basically.

441
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:27,960
 And, again, in a very, well, Palpatine, in a very manipulative.

442
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:28,960
 So, you want peace.

443
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:34,920
 You know, now we'll have the first galactic empire and now we will have peace because this is what you always wanted.

444
00:40:34,920 --> 00:40:37,380
 So, he knows how to, you know, talk to us.

445
00:40:37,380 --> 00:40:42,580
 But it's because they are such high figures that that's why they have that ripple.

446
00:40:42,580 --> 00:40:45,000
 And I think that's why you feel it galaxy-wide.

447
00:40:46,220 --> 00:40:54,440
 But at the same time, as we continue the story, you know, it is one little farm boy, you know, that ultimately brings down the empire.

448
00:40:54,440 --> 00:41:00,940
 Ultimately converts the biggest villain, who at the time is Darth Vader, back to good.

449
00:41:00,940 --> 00:41:07,780
 You know, it's just a simple farm boy who believed, who believed in the goodness of the other and of his father.

450
00:41:08,980 --> 00:41:11,900
 And who believe on the light side of the force.

451
00:41:11,900 --> 00:41:15,020
 And so, his actions do make a difference.

452
00:41:15,020 --> 00:41:19,240
 So, I think in the spiritual life, in Christian life, it's the same way.

453
00:41:19,240 --> 00:41:24,060
 So, any action, for good or for bad, has consequences throughout, you know.

454
00:41:24,060 --> 00:41:27,760
 When people ask me many times, you know, well, why do I have to go to confession?

455
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:30,800
 You know, because I could confess to God directly, you know.

456
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:31,720
 I do that every day.

457
00:41:31,720 --> 00:41:38,420
 So, at the end of the day, we Dominicans do, you know, we have a kind of examination of conscience during Compline.

458
00:41:38,420 --> 00:41:45,020
 And so, you think about the day where you failed and where you were closer to God and ask for forgiveness and so on.

459
00:41:45,020 --> 00:41:46,780
 So, yeah, we can do that every day.

460
00:41:46,780 --> 00:41:48,220
 But why do I have to go to confession?

461
00:41:48,780 --> 00:41:59,380
 And I think one of the answers is that because no matter how hidden, whatever we do, for good or for evil, has consequences throughout the galaxy, we want to call it.

462
00:41:59,380 --> 00:42:04,600
 So, when we go to confession, yeah, we're basically confessing to God.

463
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:06,080
 We're confessing to the church.

464
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:08,300
 We're confessing to each other, to another human being.

465
00:42:08,300 --> 00:42:14,400
 Because everything we do, either personal or even if it's very intimate, has consequences throughout.

466
00:42:14,400 --> 00:42:21,220
 And so, that gives us also great power because we can change the world one step at a time.

467
00:42:21,220 --> 00:42:31,760
 And, you know, even today when we see a lot of aggression, a lot of conflict and so on, just to smile in the street makes a big difference.

468
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:37,000
 Because you brought a little bit of joy to somebody in a world full of darkness, you know.

469
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:39,640
 So, it does make a difference.

470
00:42:39,640 --> 00:42:47,000
 So, any little action, you know, it's the story of the widow also that puts the little coin, you know, just a small penny, basically.

471
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:50,620
 But that may be because that was all her life that she puts in there.

472
00:42:50,620 --> 00:42:54,660
 And so, a little action does have consequences, major consequences.

473
00:42:54,660 --> 00:43:06,380
 And, Father, speaking of the consequences of Anakin's actions, the climax of Episode 3 is, of course, that iconic battle of Mustafar between Obi-Wan Kenobi.

474
00:43:06,380 --> 00:43:07,760
 And Anakin Skywalker.

475
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:15,140
 Can you speak a little bit on that conflict and that moment that takes place in the volcano planet of Mustafar?

476
00:43:15,140 --> 00:43:16,060
 Yeah, sure.

477
00:43:16,060 --> 00:43:20,980
 I mean, we see the consequences of what Anakin has chosen.

478
00:43:20,980 --> 00:43:24,740
 And so, basically, he has created hell for himself.

479
00:43:24,740 --> 00:43:26,900
 And that's why the Mustafar is like hell.

480
00:43:26,900 --> 00:43:29,400
 And so, he has become part of that.

481
00:43:30,040 --> 00:43:32,960
 And, of course, Obi-Wan still loves him.

482
00:43:32,960 --> 00:43:36,240
 You know, he tells him, you know, I loved you like a brother and so on.

483
00:43:36,240 --> 00:43:41,760
 And so, but by that time, what we see, basically, is the consequence of sin.

484
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:44,560
 And so, basically, he has closed himself in.

485
00:43:44,560 --> 00:43:58,900
 And one of the things that I think is very different from the kind of Star Wars mythology, but depends who you ask, but especially with Zen Buddhism and Taoism, is that it's not a yin-yang thing.

486
00:43:59,440 --> 00:44:04,580
 So, in the yin-yang tradition, basically, you have the evil and good that needs to be balanced.

487
00:44:04,580 --> 00:44:06,120
 That's the balance, you know.

488
00:44:06,120 --> 00:44:08,840
 And so, that somehow we have to keep the two.

489
00:44:09,500 --> 00:44:16,760
 In Christianity, for Thomas, for example, the evilness is the negation, is nothingness, you know.

490
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:19,380
 So, the good is everything, is the good.

491
00:44:19,380 --> 00:44:21,960
 And the evilness is simply nothingness.

492
00:44:21,960 --> 00:44:24,100
 And so, it's not a balanced thing.

493
00:44:24,100 --> 00:44:26,960
 It's basically the corruption of the goodness.

494
00:44:26,960 --> 00:44:30,980
 And I think George Lucas also sees that, although he tends to be more on the yin-yang.

495
00:44:31,340 --> 00:44:46,620
 But he's also saying, because even when they talk about what Anakin's supposed to be doing, which he does at the end, which is kill the emperor, kill the force of evil in the galactic empire, is to basically destroy evil.

496
00:44:46,620 --> 00:44:50,220
 So, it was not a balance of, well, we have the emperor and myself living together.

497
00:44:50,220 --> 00:44:52,180
 No, it was the destruction of evil.

498
00:44:52,180 --> 00:44:56,060
 So, ultimately, he has to have Christian perspective at the end of it.

499
00:44:56,060 --> 00:45:01,580
 So, I think that's what we're seeing in this battle between Ben Kenobi and Luke and Anakin.

500
00:45:01,580 --> 00:45:05,580
 So, Anakin has already chosen the evil side.

501
00:45:05,580 --> 00:45:08,460
 And he's so blind that simply cannot accept love.

502
00:45:08,460 --> 00:45:11,260
 I don't remember the movie right now.

503
00:45:11,260 --> 00:45:12,700
 It stars Robin Williams.

504
00:45:12,700 --> 00:45:16,460
 And I think it's May Dreams Come or something like that.

505
00:45:16,460 --> 00:45:17,620
 Yeah, May Dreams Come True.

506
00:45:17,620 --> 00:45:19,140
 Something like that.

507
00:45:19,140 --> 00:45:22,760
 I thought that was the best depiction of hell.

508
00:45:23,260 --> 00:45:26,820
 So, his wife commits suicide and she ends up in hell.

509
00:45:26,820 --> 00:45:31,680
 And, of course, the whole story is that the character of Robin Williams is trying to bring her out of hell.

510
00:45:31,680 --> 00:45:40,620
 And hell is not shown as a fiery place and that as we always usually think of hell, but it's basically like an upside down cathedral.

511
00:45:40,620 --> 00:45:42,660
 And it's just dark.

512
00:45:42,660 --> 00:45:50,420
 And she's there kind of like this, you know, like in a trauma position, fetus position and so on, just completely locked up in herself.

513
00:45:51,860 --> 00:45:53,280
 And heaven is right there.

514
00:45:53,280 --> 00:45:58,060
 So, all she needs to do is just simply stand up and walk into heaven.

515
00:45:58,060 --> 00:46:05,000
 But she's so caught up into herself, so closed in, that she cannot do that, you know.

516
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:06,700
 And so, Robin, of course, tries to do that.

517
00:46:06,700 --> 00:46:08,520
 And finally, thank goodness, he brings her back.

518
00:46:08,520 --> 00:46:11,140
 But I think that's what you see in Mustafa.

519
00:46:11,140 --> 00:46:13,540
 So, I mean, Anakin is completely closed already.

520
00:46:13,540 --> 00:46:15,660
 In his anger, in his pride.

521
00:46:16,320 --> 00:46:19,140
 He also thought he killed Padme at that time.

522
00:46:19,140 --> 00:46:21,420
 And so, he's just closed out.

523
00:46:21,420 --> 00:46:27,620
 He cannot open himself to the love of Ben and the redemption that he's offering him right there and then.

524
00:46:27,620 --> 00:46:29,880
 This is your chance to redeem yourself.

525
00:46:29,880 --> 00:46:30,800
 You know, don't do this.

526
00:46:31,320 --> 00:46:36,600
 But he's just full of anger and full of pride and blinds him to the reality.

527
00:46:36,600 --> 00:46:37,840
 So, he's closed.

528
00:46:37,840 --> 00:46:40,740
 It's the consequence of all his choices, basically.

529
00:46:40,740 --> 00:46:42,940
 And that's what we're seeing fighting right there.

530
00:46:42,940 --> 00:46:49,280
 One more chance that he could, okay, put his weapon down and join Ben Kenobi and come out and save.

531
00:46:49,520 --> 00:46:51,960
 And then he would realize Padme was fine, you know.

532
00:46:51,960 --> 00:46:54,540
 But, no, he chose himself.

533
00:46:54,540 --> 00:46:56,940
 So, that's why it reminds me also of this other movie.

534
00:46:56,940 --> 00:47:03,540
 Because, yeah, basically, in hell, somebody was saying, God continues to love us.

535
00:47:03,540 --> 00:47:05,820
 Because God is love.

536
00:47:05,820 --> 00:47:08,080
 He doesn't hate us, even in hell.

537
00:47:08,080 --> 00:47:10,860
 But it's weak who cannot respond to that.

538
00:47:10,860 --> 00:47:11,860
 We are so closed in.

539
00:47:11,860 --> 00:47:14,060
 And in one sense, that's the suffering in hell.

540
00:47:14,060 --> 00:47:17,760
 That somebody's still trying to love us, although we don't want that.

541
00:47:18,160 --> 00:47:19,960
 You know, we don't want that love.

542
00:47:19,960 --> 00:47:21,780
 And I think that's part of the suffering of hell.

543
00:47:21,780 --> 00:47:25,040
 You know, we see a little bit there on Dante's, too, Divine Comedy.

544
00:47:25,040 --> 00:47:28,480
 And I think that's what we're seeing there with Anakin Skywalker.

545
00:47:28,480 --> 00:47:34,860
 And, Father, could you speak a little bit about the different understandings in violence between the Jedi and the Sith?

546
00:47:34,860 --> 00:47:38,860
 Because there's that moment where Anakin is left burning.

547
00:47:38,860 --> 00:47:42,000
 Both arms have been cut off by Obi-Wan.

548
00:47:42,000 --> 00:47:46,060
 And Obi-Wan looks at him and has the opportunity to kill Anakin.

549
00:47:46,060 --> 00:47:51,700
 And Anakin, of course, as Darth Vader, will contribute and create a lot of suffering for everyone.

550
00:47:51,700 --> 00:47:53,000
 But he does not kill him.

551
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:59,080
 And we've seen in certain depictions in different movies and in the stories, the Sith have a very different approach to violence.

552
00:48:00,080 --> 00:48:01,040
 Yeah, I mean, definitely.

553
00:48:01,040 --> 00:48:13,760
 I think, well, first of all, like I always think, Obi-Wan Kenobi is the incarnation, almost dogmatic, of what the Jedi is supposed to be, even more than the other characters.

554
00:48:14,320 --> 00:48:17,380
 Even Yoda, I would say Yoda is the wise master.

555
00:48:17,380 --> 00:48:19,260
 Yoda is a wise master.

556
00:48:19,260 --> 00:48:22,100
 But Ben, Obi-Wan, is the rule guy.

557
00:48:22,100 --> 00:48:24,880
 You know, he's sticking to that tradition, no matter what.

558
00:48:24,880 --> 00:48:29,560
 And I think precisely at that moment, he's being a true Jedi.

559
00:48:29,560 --> 00:48:33,100
 So he will never use violence to destroy.

560
00:48:33,720 --> 00:48:39,560
 So the Jedi have always used or are supposed to use violence for defense is the last resource.

561
00:48:39,560 --> 00:48:44,520
 It's the only for defense is only to seek peace.

562
00:48:44,520 --> 00:48:48,020
 And that's why they would use weapons like the lightsaber.

563
00:48:48,020 --> 00:48:50,420
 So they would never do it for attack.

564
00:48:50,820 --> 00:48:56,860
 And so basically there, he has accomplished what he was supposed to do, bring justice.

565
00:48:56,860 --> 00:49:00,140
 So he basically stops Anakin, you know.

566
00:49:00,140 --> 00:49:05,820
 But then he leaves the judgment to the force, you know.

567
00:49:05,820 --> 00:49:08,200
 And so we in Christian life will say the same thing, you know.

568
00:49:08,200 --> 00:49:13,120
 So we are called to stop evil, but then we leave the ultimate judgment to God himself.

569
00:49:13,120 --> 00:49:14,520
 Who are we to judge?

570
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:16,180
 You know, we don't know the heart of the people.

571
00:49:16,720 --> 00:49:21,840
 And so I think that, so he did what he was as a true Jedi, he did.

572
00:49:21,840 --> 00:49:25,820
 So he just simply stopped Anakin right there and then he couldn't do anything more else.

573
00:49:25,820 --> 00:49:29,820
 Then it was up to the force that he, whether he survived or not survived.

574
00:49:29,820 --> 00:49:33,300
 He did survive, becomes even more evil, becomes Darth Vader.

575
00:49:33,300 --> 00:49:38,420
 But then he also has a spark of salvation and gets redeemed at the end.

576
00:49:38,420 --> 00:49:44,740
 So had Ben Kenobi killed him right there and then he would have died unredeemed.

577
00:49:44,740 --> 00:49:48,040
 You know, it would have been the same fate of Judas Iscariot.

578
00:49:48,040 --> 00:49:53,060
 But in any case, he didn't know what the future was going to hold for him.

579
00:49:53,060 --> 00:49:55,020
 But he said, this is not my job.

580
00:49:55,020 --> 00:49:57,660
 So this is left to the judgment of the force.

581
00:49:57,660 --> 00:49:59,200
 And that's what we are called as Christians.

582
00:49:59,200 --> 00:50:01,260
 So ultimately we're not, who am I to judge?

583
00:50:01,260 --> 00:50:02,720
 Only God can judge.

584
00:50:02,720 --> 00:50:04,800
 And so we are called to stop.

585
00:50:04,800 --> 00:50:07,020
 With regards to violence.

586
00:50:07,020 --> 00:50:10,940
 Well, yeah, I mean, I think in the Clone Wars is where it gets a little bit.

587
00:50:10,940 --> 00:50:17,960
 We don't know exactly where this is going because they are supposed to be the guardians of peace and the guardians of justice throughout the galaxy.

588
00:50:17,960 --> 00:50:21,100
 And here in the Clone Wars, we see them as generals.

589
00:50:21,100 --> 00:50:26,080
 They are the generals of the troops, the stormtroopers of the Republic troopers.

590
00:50:26,860 --> 00:50:28,860
 And so it's like a different role.

591
00:50:28,860 --> 00:50:30,560
 But again, we can see they're defending.

592
00:50:30,560 --> 00:50:31,500
 They're defending.

593
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:33,860
 And that's what the role is there for defense.

594
00:50:33,860 --> 00:50:42,820
 And we have within the Christian tradition, of course, the just war theory and so on, which is the ultimate, you know, this is the last thing we can do.

595
00:50:42,820 --> 00:50:48,160
 And it's only for to stop, to defend and to search for peace and justice.

596
00:50:48,500 --> 00:50:50,620
 Whereas the Jedi use it for aggression.

597
00:50:50,620 --> 00:50:56,520
 So it's basically they use the force, the violence to accomplish their power.

598
00:50:56,520 --> 00:51:01,300
 And so they're using for conquest to control, to expand their power.

599
00:51:01,300 --> 00:51:05,300
 And so it's a very different, and that would not be a Christian way, so at all.

600
00:51:05,300 --> 00:51:08,560
 And so, yeah, I know that some people have criticized the Jedi.

601
00:51:08,560 --> 00:51:14,360
 But I just read an article, which was very, very interesting, which I didn't even really see it until I read the article.

602
00:51:14,360 --> 00:51:29,840
 It was Luke Skywalker, and so he has to learn the same lesson, that basically when he sees Yoda for the first time in Dagobah, and he's expecting this great warrior, and he says, wars do not make a man great, because that's not the point.

603
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:37,140
 You know, the point is peace and balance and so on, and everything that Yoda incarnates there in Dagobah and teaches Luke.

604
00:51:37,140 --> 00:51:39,040
 And Luke eventually learns.

605
00:51:39,240 --> 00:51:48,820
 And so when he has to confront his father, he refuses to use force, because if he gets attacked, then he defends himself.

606
00:51:48,820 --> 00:51:53,880
 But basically, no, I'm not going to fight you, he says, because this is not the way of the Jedi.

607
00:51:53,880 --> 00:52:00,060
 You know, also when he has the opportunity to kill Palpatine, he will not do it, because this is not the way of it.

608
00:52:00,060 --> 00:52:04,420
 So he has learned that pacifism, basically, is the way of the Jedi.

609
00:52:04,420 --> 00:52:11,620
 And in the new trilogy, which, I mean, I still have to reanalyze again, because I'm not too sure.

610
00:52:11,620 --> 00:52:14,260
 But anyway, this article was talking about this.

611
00:52:14,260 --> 00:52:23,220
 So when Rey calls him to come back to fight the resistance, he will not do it, is because he has said, this is, the violence is not the way.

612
00:52:23,220 --> 00:52:25,520
 That's not the way of the Jedi, you know.

613
00:52:25,980 --> 00:52:29,460
 And so, and she expects him to come back, so he will be a warrior.

614
00:52:29,460 --> 00:52:31,500
 And that's her vision of the Jedi.

615
00:52:31,500 --> 00:52:37,000
 And so where they're talking to each other, whatever, it's like, yeah, you don't understand what the Jedi are.

616
00:52:37,000 --> 00:52:39,620
 We're not, that's not what we are, you know.

617
00:52:39,620 --> 00:52:42,100
 So it's to bring balance to the forces.

618
00:52:42,100 --> 00:52:44,720
 So it's more of a pacifist outlook.

619
00:52:44,720 --> 00:52:47,500
 And I think Luke incarnates there.

620
00:52:47,620 --> 00:52:52,820
 There's other things that happened there in the last movie, but basically that's what the article was saying.

621
00:52:52,820 --> 00:52:54,280
 And yeah, I kind of agree.

622
00:52:54,280 --> 00:52:58,840
 And so, and I think that's why also Obi-Wan did not kill.

623
00:52:58,840 --> 00:53:05,360
 So it was, he only performed justice and would not take revenge and so on.

624
00:53:05,360 --> 00:53:08,220
 And so, and he then left the judgment to the force.

625
00:53:09,220 --> 00:53:23,760
 Father, when you look at this, you know, ultimately long arc to redemption, even if what appears to be the story of Anakin is quite sad and very dark, what takeaways can we take from this?

626
00:53:23,760 --> 00:53:28,740
 What can we learn from Anakin's journey versus Luke's, for example?

627
00:53:28,740 --> 00:53:29,920
 Well, I mean, I think, yeah.

628
00:53:29,920 --> 00:53:33,200
 So I think that's what we need to do, almost see the two of them.

629
00:53:33,200 --> 00:53:35,080
 You have to see Anakin and you have to see Luke.

630
00:53:35,660 --> 00:53:40,840
 Because again, both, so the whole arc shows, none of us are perfect.

631
00:53:40,840 --> 00:53:43,080
 So we all have virtues and we all have vices.

632
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:44,520
 Nobody's perfect.

633
00:53:44,520 --> 00:53:56,780
 But it's how you live your life, how you are making your decisions, you know, towards the light or towards the darkness, you know, to the dark side of the force or to the light side of the force.

634
00:53:56,780 --> 00:53:58,960
 And that makes a difference, you know.

635
00:54:00,680 --> 00:54:13,320
 The difference, I think, of course, between the Star Wars universe is that a lot of them, for them, it's a lot of, it's me through will and training and so on that I do the good or I do the bad.

636
00:54:13,320 --> 00:54:16,880
 And as Christians, we know that ultimately we depend upon God.

637
00:54:16,880 --> 00:54:19,220
 So it's God ultimately that's helping us.

638
00:54:19,220 --> 00:54:24,340
 But we need to be cooperative with that, to collaborate with the force, basically.

639
00:54:24,780 --> 00:54:26,520
 And so to be open to that.

640
00:54:26,520 --> 00:54:29,440
 And so that, I think that's a difference there.

641
00:54:29,440 --> 00:54:35,400
 But basically, but both Christianity and the Star Wars series, choices are important.

642
00:54:35,400 --> 00:54:37,320
 And what choices do we make?

643
00:54:37,320 --> 00:54:39,960
 And yes, and from where do we make those choices?

644
00:54:39,960 --> 00:54:41,040
 Because we all have fears.

645
00:54:41,040 --> 00:54:42,620
 We all have pride, et cetera.

646
00:54:42,620 --> 00:54:44,140
 But how do we choose?

647
00:54:44,140 --> 00:54:46,480
 Do we channel those for the good?

648
00:54:46,720 --> 00:54:49,960
 Or basically, we try to control that, try to repress it.

649
00:54:49,960 --> 00:54:52,080
 And then that brings us to destruction.

650
00:54:52,080 --> 00:54:54,880
 And I think that's what both Anakin and Luke show.

651
00:54:54,880 --> 00:55:01,720
 So Anakin basically keeps choosing to control it, to have the power, et cetera.

652
00:55:01,720 --> 00:55:03,120
 And so the dark side.

653
00:55:03,120 --> 00:55:09,180
 And so then that leads to the ultimate, him becoming Darth Vader, somebody who's completely different.

654
00:55:09,560 --> 00:55:14,540
 Whereas Luke is always, you know, here and there, he's always choosing the good.

655
00:55:14,540 --> 00:55:16,060
 He's going forward, forward.

656
00:55:16,060 --> 00:55:19,960
 And we see that till the end, to the point then that he can save his own father.

657
00:55:19,960 --> 00:55:25,200
 So it's not just a question of saving himself, because he also saw that in the cave in Dagobah.

658
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:26,660
 He could have done otherwise.

659
00:55:26,660 --> 00:55:30,480
 So he also has to kind of redeem himself or be redeemed.

660
00:55:30,740 --> 00:55:35,820
 But at the same time, now he has reached a certain level where he can redeem somebody else.

661
00:55:35,820 --> 00:55:37,180
 And he redeems his father.

662
00:55:37,180 --> 00:55:42,080
 And so that's the final teaching of both Star Wars.

663
00:55:42,080 --> 00:55:44,740
 Wow, this has been a fascinating conversation.

664
00:55:44,740 --> 00:55:46,680
 Do you have any final thoughts you'd like to share?

665
00:55:46,680 --> 00:55:56,640
 Well, I mean, I think it's, I mean, stories like Star Wars and any kind of mythical stories, I think, yeah, they're not the Christian gospel.

666
00:55:56,800 --> 00:56:02,160
 But I think they do deal with topics that the whole world deals with.

667
00:56:02,160 --> 00:56:11,080
 You know, the question of vice and virtue, of good and evil, light and darkness, making choices, redemption.

668
00:56:11,080 --> 00:56:20,180
 I think that's what this great epics, not only Star Wars, but other epics that we have in culture and so on, teaches us.

669
00:56:20,180 --> 00:56:25,460
 And they're important to study them and to look at them and then compare them to the gospel epic that we have.

670
00:56:26,100 --> 00:56:28,700
 And how that also enlightens us.

671
00:56:28,700 --> 00:56:43,120
 And I think the main takeaway, both from Star Wars and Christianity, is that nobody can fall so deep into the dark side that ultimately cannot be brought to the light side.

672
00:56:43,120 --> 00:56:48,720
 So there's nobody that can fall so much into vice, et cetera, that cannot be redeemed at the end.

673
00:56:48,720 --> 00:56:51,880
 And I think that's both the new hope.

674
00:56:51,880 --> 00:56:53,800
 That is so important.

675
00:56:53,800 --> 00:56:55,340
 Father, this has been wonderful.

676
00:56:55,340 --> 00:56:57,080
 I hope we can do it again soon.

677
00:56:57,080 --> 00:56:58,240
 Thank you, very good.

